<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>have a good head • have a good mind</xh5><p> <i>have a good head—</i>1. <i>(also: have a good head on one’s shoulders)</i> be smart and intelligent: I searched for Ann, because she <u>has a good head</u> and knows a lot about medicine. 2. <i>(for)</i> have a special talent in a certain area: You’ve <u>got a good head</u> for business, Thompson. It’s the rest of you that worries me. 3. said of beer with good foam at the top: It was the first brasserie to captivate Jean ... it still retains the flavor of Alsace, where the beer always <u>has a good head.</u></p><p> <i>have a good mind</i>—(followed by Infinitive) be strongly inclined to do smth.: I <u>have a good mind</u> to find these identity thieves and ask how they’re getting money out of my account.</p> </entry>
